<django_security_guide>
<title>DJANGO SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Django's "batteries included" approach provides built-in security features, but misconfigurations and improper usage can lead to SQL injection, XSS, CSRF bypass, and authentication vulnerabilities. Testing must focus on ORM bypass, template injection, settings exposure, and authentication/session handling.</critical>

<scope>
- ORM injection and raw SQL vulnerabilities
- Template injection and auto-escaping bypass
- CSRF protection bypass
- Authentication and session management
- Admin panel security
- DEBUG mode and settings exposure
- File upload and path traversal
- REST framework vulnerabilities
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify Django version and installed apps through fingerprinting.
2. Test ORM queries for injection via extra(), raw(), and RawSQL.
3. Probe template rendering for auto-escaping bypass.
4. Test authentication views and session handling.
5. Examine admin panel and REST API endpoints.
</methodology>

